    "sections": [
      {
        "title": "About",
        "content": "<p>The 21st Century Integrated Digital Experience Act (IDEA), enacted in December 2018, mandates that U.S. federal agencies modernize their websites, digitize services and forms, adopt e-signatures, enhance customer experience, and standardize shared services. In September 2023, the Office of Management and Budget issued Memo M-23-22 to further guide agencies in implementing these requirements, aiming to provide a digital-first public experience that meets modern expectations.</p>"
      }
    ],
    "links": [
      {
        "link": "https://www.congress.gov/bill/115th-congress/house-bill/5759/text",
        "text": "Website"
      },
      {
        "link": "https://congress.gov/",
        "text": "U.S. Congress"
      }
    ],
    "audio": "https://docs.scangov.org/assets/audio/21st-century-idea.mp3"
  },
  "28-cfr-part-35": {
    "displayName": "28 CFR Part 35",
    "description": "State and local government web accessibility requirements.",
